exif: {"Image ImageDescription": "Vintage engraving of the Lightship at the Nore, 1857. The Nore is a sandbank at the mouth of the Thames Estuary, England. It marks the point where the River Thames meets the North Sea. The Nore is a hazard to shipping, so in 1732 the world's first lightship was moored over it.", "Image Copyright": "duncan1890"}
